  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison rejoices at the willingness of his sister-in-law (Sarah Thurber Benson) to visit them. He describes the furnished house they expect to inhabit. Garrison is in a state of excitement, and his scrofulous complaint grows worse. The solemnity of the Peace Convention was disturbed by the irresistible humor of William Ladd. Ladd is a &quot;huge and strange compound of fat, good nature, and benevolence.&quot;</subfield>
